# 2277 - if else
# Compare two characters, output 1 if same, 0 if different

# Read first character into A
A<I
# Read second character into B
B<I

# Use C as base address (128)
C<128

# Clear addresses we'll use: [C+A] and [C+B]
[C+A]<0
[C+B]<0

# Set [C+A] to 1
[C+A]<1

# Read from [C+B] into D
# If A == B, D will be 1, else 0
D<[C+B]

# Output ASCII '1' (49) if D==1, else '0' (48)
# Use lookup table: store 48 at address 0, 49 at address 1
[0]<48
[1]<49

# Read from address [D] to get ASCII value
D<[D]

# Output D
O<D

# Halt
Z<1
